properties.name: The days are getting warmer now, lots of sunscreen and long sleeve shirts to protect us from the sunshine :) -Mia
﻿Happy Birthday Andy! We’re giving you a big cheer from the middle of the Atlantic. -Mia & the FALKEN crew
Paolo took over the new speed record from Jillian, new record is 16.3 kts!
We changed our local boat time last night and are now UTC -1 onboard.
﻿Breakfast quesadillas for Team A from last nights left overs, yum! We need one improvement though for FALKEN’s cockpit; a piri piri hot sauce holder :) -Mia
Freshly baked chocolate chip cookies, we wonder how long time it takes before the off-watch wakes up by the wonderful smell of baking :) Thank you Jillian!
Spaghetti bolognaise for dinner. 2 reefs in the main, and we are still making 9-10 kts! -Mia
﻿Engine on, pole down. We can sail in light wind, but when the true wind drops below 5kts, it’s not much we can do. Another dolphin show during dinner! -Mia
Just a wonderful day today, sunshine and downwind sailing!
On course to Antigua. Light winds but expecting it to fill in soon. Woohoo! Shout out to Skipper Mum Sheila Caruso - Emily

Nothing feels better than a shower offshore! The watermaker is making water and with full tanks we treated the crew to a shower at the stern! Vilgot is cooking up a storm in the galley, chicken fajitas is on the menu! -Mia
﻿Freshly baked scones with crème cheese and jam for breakfast! Wind is up, we’re sailing fast - happy crew :D -Mia

17/1 18.48 UTC: Lasagna for dinner. Pole up, downwind sailing at 7-8 kts.
-Mia
Hurricane eggs 2.0! Topped with a slice of cheese, yum! -Mia
Dolphins at the bow!
Gybe ho! Home straight. E x
Wind picking up - putting a reef in! Also at the same time: pancakes for breakfast!
Beautiful night with stars and finally the moon! - Mia
﻿500nm in 48 hours. Now that’s trucking!!!
Poled out!!! Whoop whoop!!
Could not ask for a nicer day, wind 18-20 kts, downwind sailing and blue sky. But the best is that the cockpit is shaded by the sails by now!
Wind a bit lighter today, 12-17 kts of wind, beautiful sailing into the sunset! -Mia

﻿It’s a bit tricky steering in the dark with no moon and overcast, but we are moving along nicely at 7-8 kts! Many cups of tea and some snack to keep us awake these first few night before we are adjusted to the watch schedule -Mia
Sailed over 1000 nm miles now! -Mia
Downwind sailing, blue sky and cockpit showers!
WHALES! Just before dinner, we spotted 5-6 whales just off our port side! Kevin even got a photo of it! -Mia
Moon just came up around 5.30 boat time, a tiny sliver. Crew is doing a fantastic job on the helm desperately the darkness, surfing down waves at 12 -13 kts at times.
Dark nights, 4 am boat time and moon is not yet up!  Overcast but once in a while some stars shines through the clouds -Mia

18/1 19.54 UTC: Great day of sailing, we even managed to sail though some
light patches. And we had some dolphins come for a visit earlier today. -
Mia
You can feel we are getting closer to the Caribbean now, hot hot hot! At least the nights are cool, and the sun is hiding behind the sails towards the afternoon!

17/1  15.00 UTC: FALKEN is under way! We left Las Palmas around 11 this
morning, hoisted the sails just outside the harbor and have had a wonderful
sail down the Canary coast. Sunshine and 10-12 kts of breeze - Mia
Finally a sky full of stars!
Made our turn west and are heading for Antigua!
Great sailing, 20-25 kts of true wind, blue sky and occasional squalls. 223 nm sailed the last 24 hrs! -Mia
